## ModusNavbar Custom Content Slots

The navbar supports `centerContent` and `endContent` slots for injecting custom elements (project name, action buttons, etc.):

```tsx
<ModusNavbar
  userCard={{ name: "Jane Smith", email: "jane@trimble.com" }}
  visibility={{ mainMenu: false, notifications: true, apps: true, help: true, user: true }}
  centerContent={<div class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">Project Name</div>}
  endContent={<ModusButton color="primary" size="sm" variant="outlined">Invite members</ModusButton>}
/>
```

Set `visibility.mainMenu: false` when using a custom sidebar instead of the built-in hamburger menu.

---

## ModusSideNavigation Limitations

`ModusSideNavigation` only supports a **flat `MenuItem[]`** array. It does NOT support:
- Nested or hierarchical menu items
- Expandable sub-sections (e.g., "Records" expanding to show "RFIs", "Submittals", etc.)
- Grouped navigation with section headers
- Custom active state styling (it uses its own internal styling)

**If you need nested/hierarchical navigation**, build a custom sidebar using:
- `div` elements for items with `<i class="modus-icons">` for icons
- `createSignal<boolean>` per expandable section for open/close state
- CSS `max-height` transition with `overflow-hidden` for expand/collapse animation
- `@solidjs/router`'s `useLocation()` to detect active path
- Active styling: `bg-primary-20 text-primary border-l-2 border-primary`
- Design system colors only (`text-foreground-80`, `hover:bg-muted`, `border-bottom-default`)

---

## Common Pitfalls

1. **Menu item icons not showing** - Use `<i class="modus-icons" slot="start-icon">name</i>` child element, not the `startIcon` property
2. **Trimble logo broken on deep routes** - Ensure asset copy targets both `modus-wc/assets` and `assets` directories
3. **Two demo sections interfere** - Use separate components with independent signal state
4. **Side nav expands the page width** - Wrap in `overflow-hidden` container with fixed height
5. **Events not firing** - Use `addEventListener` in `onMount` for web component custom events
6. **Need nested navigation** - ModusSideNavigation only supports flat items; build a custom sidebar for hierarchical menus

